title: A Fall of Moondust.mp3
description:
A full length radio play based on the Arthur C Clarke story.

A group of tourists on the moon are on an excursion to the Mountains of Inaccessibility via the Sea of Thirst when a moonquake causes the ground to open swallowing up their craft. Nobody knows exactly where they are - this story was written presumably before the invention of GPS tracking - and their air supply is limited. Can they be rescued in time?
